<br>
How long did it take you to get the Stein, Torch, and Broom components for your focus item quests?<br>
<br>
I only ask because I have been camping the Magicians in Najena for about 12 hours total now and all I have gotten is the Shovel...<br>
<br>
These items seem to be ULTRA rare drops.<br>
<br>
Any feedback and help would be appreciated. Thanks!  <p>----------------------------------------------- <br>
Magnamar<br>
Guildmaster of the Phoenix Legion<br>
Mage of the 10th Circle</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ucashmason.showPublicProfile?language=EN>cashmason</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 82<br> <font color=#333333>(4/6/01 3:54 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerequipmentandquests.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=651.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Focus Item Quests</span><hr size=1> took me about 40 hours. you can also get them from the aligators in cazic thule. and since many more players go there you can auction for the pieecs you need<br>
<br>
Dantes 58 th mage <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/usedonus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sedonus</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_cyanspot.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 5<br> <font color=#333333>(4/6/01 12:40 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerequipmentandquests.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=651.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.thedragonnetwork.net/tdnmini.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Focus Item Quests</span><hr size=1> Took my 33 bard about 10 - 11 hours total (in Najena).  Just got the torch lastnight (the last item I needed).  It probably helps that my bard has an easy time of the magicians.  It also helps that I'm almost always alone in the entire dungeon (7th Hammer).  On occasion there will be 2 or 3 others, but only once has there been one other seeking the items, and he was around for only 30 minutes or so.<br>
<br>
Anyhow, went well for me.  Because of lack of competition with other players I would make my rounds through Najena taking out each Magi one at a time (the would never agro me at my level, so I could pick off the group of 3 one at a time hehe) and then I would go kill the 2 Darkbones in the prison area where the princess is.  I got my shovel off one of those. <br>
<br>
BTW, if you happen to be on 7th Hammer, I have a spare broom.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
